=>"3117", :strong_definition=>"Strong's Hebrew 3117: 1) day, time, year <BR> 1a) day (as opposed to night) <BR> 1b) day (24 hour period) <BR> 1b1) as defined by evening and morning in Genesis 1 <BR> 1b2) as a division of time <BR> 1b2a) a working day, a day's journey <BR> 1c) days, lifetime (pl.) <BR> 1d) time, period (general) <BR> 1e) year <BR> 1f) temporal references <BR> 1f1) today <BR> 1f2) yesterday <BR> 1f3) tomorrow"}}, {:source=>{:book=>"genesis", :chapter=>3, :verse=>17, :reference=>"genesis 3:17", :text=>"of your life"}, :hebrew=>{:word=>"׃ָךיֶּֽיַח", :translit=>"ḥay-ye-ḵā.", :defined=>"chai·Yei·cha.: life ", :stats=>[{:occurance=>"2", :total=>"12"}]}, :strongs=>{:strong_number=>"2416", :strong_definition=>"Strong's Hebrew 2416: adj <BR> 1) living, alive <BR> 1a) green (of vegetation) <BR> 1b) flowing, fresh (of water) <BR> 1c) lively, active (of man) <BR> 1d) reviving (of the springtime) <BR> n m <BR> 2) relatives <BR> 3) life (abstract emphatic) <BR> 3a) life <BR> 3b) sustenance, maintenance <BR> n f <BR> 4) living thing, animal <BR> 4a) animal <BR> 4b) life <BR> 4c) appetite <BR> 4d) revival, renewal <BR> 5) community"}}], :versions=>[{:version=>"New International Version", :text=>"To Adam he said, \"Because you listened to your wife and ate fruit from the tree about which I commanded you, 'You must not eat from it,' \"Cursed is the ground because of you; through painful toil you will eat food from it all the days of your life."}, {:version=>"New Living Translation", :text=>"And to the man he said, “Since you listened to your wife and ate from the tree whose fruit I commanded you not to eat, the ground is cursed because of you. All your life you will struggle to scratch a living from it."}, {:version=>"English Standard Version", :text=>"And to Adam he said, “Because you have listened to the voice of your wife and have eaten of the tree of which I commanded you, ‘You shall not eat of it,’ cursed is the ground because of you; in pain you shall eat of it all the days of your life;"}, {:version=>"Berean Study Bible", :text=>"And to Adam He said: “Because you have listened to the voice of your wife and have eaten from the tree of which I commanded you not to eat, cursed is the ground because of you; through toil you will eat of it all the days of your life."}, {:version=>"New American Standard Bible ", :text=>"Then to Adam He said, \"Because you have listened to the voice of your wife, and have eaten from the tree about which I commanded you, saying, 'You shall not eat from it'; Cursed is the ground because of you; In toil you will eat of it All the days of your life."}, {:version=>"New King James Version", :text=>"Then to Adam He said, “Because you have heeded the voice of your wife, and have eaten from the tree of which I commanded you, saying, ‘You shall not eat of it’: “Cursed "}, {:version=>" the ground for your sake; In toil you shall eat ", :text=>" it All the days of your life."}, {:version=>"King James Bible", :text=>"And unto Adam he said, Because thou hast hearkened unto the voice of thy wife, and hast eaten of the tree, of which I commanded thee, saying, Thou shalt not eat of it: cursed "}, {:version=>" the ground for thy sake; in sorrow shalt thou eat ", :text=>" it all the days of thy life;"}, {:version=>"Christian Standard Bible", :text=>"And he said to the man, \"Because you listened to your wife and ate from the tree about which I commanded you, 'Do not eat from it': The ground is cursed because of you. You will eat from it by means of painful labor all the days of your life."}, {:version=>"Contemporary English Version", :text=>"The LORD said to the man, \"You listened to your wife and ate the fruit I told you not to eat. And so, the ground will be under a curse because of what you did. As long as you live, you will have to struggle to grow enough food. "}, {:version=>"Good News Translation", :text=>"And he said to the man, \"You listened to your wife and ate the fruit which I told you not to eat. Because of what you have done, the ground will be under a curse. You will have to work hard all your life to make it produce enough food for you. "}, {:version=>"Holman Christian Standard Bible", :text=>"And He said to Adam, \"Because you listened to your wife's voice and ate from the tree about which I commanded you, 'Do not eat from it: The ground is cursed because of you. You will eat from it by means of painful labor all the days of your life. "}, {:version=>"International Standard Version", :text=>"He told the man, \"Because you have listened to what your wife said, and have eaten from the tree about which I commanded you, 'You must not eat from it,' cursed is the ground because of you. You'll eat from it through pain-filled labor for the rest of your life."}, {:version=>"NET Bible", :text=>"But to Adam he said, \"Because you obeyed your wife and ate from the tree about which I commanded you, 'You must not eat from it,' cursed is the ground thanks to you; in painful toil you will eat of it all the days of your life. "}, {:version=>"New Heart English Bible", :text=>"To Adam he said, \"Because you have listened to your wife's voice, and have eaten of the tree, of which I commanded you, saying, 'You shall not eat of it,' cursed is the ground for your sake. In toil you will eat of it all the days of your life."}, {:version=>"GOD'S WORD® Translation", :text=>"Then he said to the man, \"You listened to your wife and ate fruit from the tree, although I commanded you, 'You must never eat its fruit.' The ground is cursed because of you. Through hard work you will eat [food that comes] from it every day of your life."}, {:version=>"JPS Tanakh 1917", :text=>"And unto Adam He said: 'Because thou hast hearkened unto the voice of thy wife, and hast eaten of the tree, of which I commanded thee, saying: Thou shalt not eat of it; cursed is the ground for thy sake; in toil shalt thou eat of it all the days of thy life."}, {:version=>"New American Standard 1977 ", :text=>"Then to Adam He said, “Because you have listened to the voice of your wife, and have eaten from the tree about which I commanded you, saying, ‘You shall not eat from it’; Cursed is the ground because of you; In toil you shall eat of it All the days of your life."}, {:version=>"King James 2000 Bible", :text=>"And unto Adam he said, Because you have listened unto the voice of your wife, and have eaten of the tree, of which I commanded you, saying, You shall not eat of it: cursed is the ground for your sake; in sorrow shall you eat of it all the days of your life;"}, {:version=>"American King James Version", :text=>"And to Adam he said, Because you have listened to the voice of your wife, and have eaten of the tree, of which I commanded you, saying, You shall not eat of it: cursed is the ground for your sake; in sorrow shall you eat of it all the days of your life;"}, {:version=>"American Standard Version", :text=>"And unto Adam he said, Because thou hast hearkened unto the voice of thy wife, and hast eaten of the tree, of which I commanded thee, saying, Thou shalt not eat of it: cursed is the ground for thy sake; in toil shalt thou eat of it all the days of thy life;"}, {:version=>"Brenton Septuagint Translation", :text=>"And to Adam he said, Because thou hast hearkened to the voice of thy wife, and eaten of the tree concerning which I charged thee of it only not to eat—of that thou hast eaten, cursed "}, {:version=>" the ground in thy labours, in pain shalt thou eat of it all the days of thy life.", :text=>"Douay-Rheims Bible"}, {:version=>"And to Adam he said: Because thou hast hearkened to the voice of thy wife, and hast eaten of the tree, whereof I commanded thee that thou shouldst not eat, cursed is the earth in thy work; with labour and toil shalt thou eat thereof all the days of thy life. ", :text=>"Darby Bible Translation"}, {:version=>"And to Adam he said, Because thou hast hearkened to the voice of thy wife, and eaten of the tree of which I commanded thee saying, Thou shalt not eat of it: cursed be the ground on thy account; with toil shalt thou eat [of] it all the days of thy life;", :text=>"English Revised Version"}, {:version=>"And unto Adam he said, Because thou hast hearkened unto the voice of thy wife, and hast eaten of the tree, of which I commanded thee, saying, Thou shalt not eat of it: cursed is the ground for thy sake; in toil shalt thou eat of it all the days of thy life;", :text=>"Webster's Bible Translation"}, {:version=>"And to Adam he said, Because thou hast hearkened to the voice of thy wife, and hast eaten of the tree of which I commanded thee, saying, Thou shalt not eat of it: cursed is the ground for thy sake; in sorrow shalt thou eat of it all the days of thy life;", :text=>"World English Bible"}, {:version=>"To Adam he said, \"Because you have listened to your wife's voice, and have eaten of the tree, of which I commanded you, saying, 'You shall not eat of it,' cursed is the ground for your sake. In toil you will eat of it all the days of your life.", :text=>"Young's Literal Translation"}, {:version=>" And to the man He said, 'Because thou hast hearkened to the voice of thy wife, and dost eat of the tree concerning which I have charged thee, saying, Thou dost not eat of it, cursed is the ground on thine account; in sorrow thou dost eat of it all days of thy life,", :text=>nil}]}